Try the following Nginx config to block access to a subdirectory when its name is unknown:

```
location ~ /users/.*/public/ {
    allow all;
    try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
}

location /users/ {
    deny all;
}
```

This uses a regular expression to match unknown subdirectories and a common location to block access to the `/users/` directory.

