To establish a 1:0..1 relationship between the same models in EF Code-First, use the following configuration:

- For 1:1 relationship (one module has one special resource, but a resource can be special for many modules):
```csharp
public class Module { ... public Resource SpecialResource { get; set; } }
public class Resource { ... public Module Module { get; set; } }
modelBuilder.Entity<Resource>().HasOptional(x => x.Module).WithOptionalDependent(x => x.SpecialResource);
```

- For 1:0..1 relationship (one module has one special resource, but a resource can only be special for one module):
```csharp
public class Module { ... public int? SpecialResourceId { get; set; } public Resource SpecialResource { get; set; } }
public class Resource { ... public int? ModuleId { get; set; } public Module Module { get; set; } }
modelBuilder.Entity<Module>().HasMany(x => x.Resources).WithOptional(x => x.Module).HasForeignKey(x => x.ModuleId);
modelBuilder.Entity<Resource>().HasOptional(x => x.IsSpecialForModule).WithOptionalDependent(x => x.SpecialResource);
```

